	<p>To learn to create numbers in Ido, you must first get familiar with two new interfixes: "a" and "e"! These can not be seen elswhere in the language, and you should not mix them up with "a" and "e" which means "to" and "and"! These "a" and "e" represent "multiplied by" and "plus"! So, for example: if I would like to say fourty six (46), I will start with the beginning, with the biggest number; "4", now in this example, we don't want a simple "4"!, we need it ten time bigger... what do we do? I'll tell you: we take quar (4), add the "a" I told you about earlier, and attach "dek" (ten) after these two! Then we have "quaradek"! "quaradek" means "40", so almost there; we just need a "6"! Then what we do; is that we take the quaradek, and the "e" from earlier, and attach "sis" (6) after and get quaradekesis! Now, in Ido we attach "-" before and after every "e" (but never the "a"s!) and get quaradek-e-sis! All done!</p>
